This paper focuses on cyber threat intelligence and proposes a framework for modelling the behavioural aspect of an attacker. It also introduces a novel semi-supervised algorithm called Fusion Hidden Markov Model (FHMM) for better modelling of temporal relationships in data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper also uses machine learning techniques such as ensemble learning and deep recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also deals with data analysis and modelling, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
